Red Star Express Plc, one of Nigeria’s foremost logistics solutions providers, has celebrated the women in its workforce as part of its recent celebrations for the International Women’s Day . The company, in a statement expressed its appreciation for the women in the company; stating that their contributions to its growth cannot be overemphasised. “Red Star Express Plc has always been at the forefront of the discussion regarding equality. We have always believed in providing equal career opportunities for individuals; regardless of race, religion, tribe, or gender. The women in our workforce represent a crucial part of our business as we have a number of them in key leadership positions within the company. Their contribution to our growth over the years has been immense and we will continue to be supportive of their advancement in the workplace”. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Red Star Express Plc is a Licensee of Federal Express (FedEx) Corporation, the world’s largest delivery solutions provider. It has over 150 offices in Nigeria; with international offices in Niger Republic, Burkina Faso and Benin Republic. Its network spans over 1,500 communities in Nigeria and 214 countries worldwide. BUA Founder, Rabiu, Donates N200m To Sokoto State University NAHCO Challenges Women On Productivity, Gives Cash Rewards Red Star Express Plc is made up of 4 divisions and business units specialising in areas such as Express Delivery, Logistics, Freight, Outsourcing services, Supply Chain Management, e-Commerce Facilitation, Printing and Packaging, EArchiving, as well as Agro Trade Logistics.